  "description": "How Connect speaks to Swarm as a reactor IChannel: the three-layer split, pure-transport role, and the push/pull cycles that keep PGlite and feeds aligned.",
  "orientation": "The Swarm Channel is Connect's decentralized sync transport: a reactor IChannel implementation that routes operations through Bee feeds and /bytes instead of Switchboard GraphQL. Notes in this MOC document the three-layer split (bee-reactor-adapter, SwarmChannel, plugin), the IChannel mailbox contract that keeps the channel pure-transport, and the paired push/pull cycles that encrypt, upload, publish, and later decrypt operation batches. The cluster also covers multi-remote reactor support, the bridge role between Switchboard and Swarm, and the debounced health/status surface. Together these notes describe the full architecture that Path A depends on \u2014 the plugin-resident transport the user-confirmed end state requires.",
